text_options.text:
Purpose

The purpose of this document is to identify the departments, systems and reports utilized in the Close the Books process and provide guidance on evidential matter and process / control owner responsibilities and management's judgment in documenting and sustaining a functioning internal control environment.

Departments, Systems and Reports
•[parg]Departments affecting this process
[parg][parg]•[parg]The Accounting function is responsible for:
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Preparing month-end journal entries and reconciling balance sheet accounts
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Producing monthly, quarterly, annual financial reports and related financial schedules / 	[parg][parg][parg]supporting documentation
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Preparing and filing the necessary SEC filing requirements (10-Qs, 10K, etc.)
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Vender or Service Provider analysis (SSAE 16 / SOC 1 review)
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Reporting and Electronic Audit Evidence
•[parg]Systems utilized in this process are:
[parg][parg]•[parg]Oracle, EPM
[parg]Reports - Insmed utilizes the following reports in the Financial Reporting Process and has identified those reports below;
[parg][parg]•[parg]System Generated
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]General Ledger Trial Balance
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Balance Sheet
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Income Statement
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]CFO Report by Department
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Stock Based Compensation Report
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Posted Journal Report
[parg][parg]•[parg]Manual
[parg][parg][parg][parg]•[parg]Various Reconciliations

The Finance department's monthly close process includes reconciliations and other data that is analyzed, reviewed and utilized as evidence to support the controls within Financial Reporting Process. Inherently the account reconciliations will support the completeness and accuracy of the account balances and be substantiated by copies of appropriate support (i.e. documents and/or calculations).
